Local Variables:
-----------------
1. Any variable defined with in the scope are called local variable to that scope.

2. Local variables can be used only within that scope .

3. Local variables cannot be accessed outside the scope.

Global Variables:
-----------------
1. Any variable defined outside the scope are called global variables.

2. Global variable can be accessed with in the scope and outside the scope.


Example :

	Integer age ;
	String name;
	{
		String branch;
		String city;
		age=40;
		name='Kiran';
	}

	Local variables : branch,city 
	Global variables: age ,name


Example : 
	class Example {
		String name;
		String phone;
		String city;
		void show()
		{
			String branch;
			String industry;

			branch='SRNagar';
			industry='Banking';
			name='Wipro';
			phone='040-1234';
			city='Hyd';
		}
		void callMe()
		{
			String rating='Hot';
			city='Ban';
		}
	}

==> Show :  
	Local : branch,industry
	global : name,phone,city



==> CallMe : 
	Local : rating 
	global: name,phone,city



 
